,Recommended,313010,14346359,"Posted: 5 February, 2015",all,Swoy,"New info added! seeNEW:tags below.IntroductionWell, to start with, I have played all CXL there is, from the very first one to this - very last one. And I will have to say that this is however worth the money for once. I am actually impressed by the small things I have been annoyed by in earlier iterations of this franchise. Let me sumarize briefly what elements they've improved, and what is not changed about the game.ImprovementsThis is my list of things I have considered annoying for the past few games, and the status of their current state.AnnoyanceDescriptionStateCommentRoadsnappingOdd or erronous roadsnapping makes laying roads difficult and is sometimes a tedious jobFixedFrom my perspective this is fixed. I have tried to place roads on top of roads, build tunnels under districts and placed bridges in places not possible in previous iterations. It feels more natural now, which is good enough for me.Traffic jamWhen building a block or a few streets, and want to allow the citizens commute to work, you end up with traffic jams all over the place and those ""real life""- scenarios wont work as expected. Forcing expressways where a normal avenue should have sufficed.Fixed and FixedAt least, it seems better now, after making a few neighbourhoods as i normally would do, the difference is clear from CXL and CXXL, the traffic flow is just that much better, and I can focus on infrastructure the way it should have been from the start.PollutionIndustry and car pollution either grow to fast or is totally out of proportions from the start.FixedThis is where I actually became the most surprised! Things work so much better now, they've tweaked the industry so that the polution is less problematic where you expect it. And if you place coal-plants, they polute exactly how I expect them to.MenusThe menus lack certain areas, such as achievements - and they are extremely laggy and can sometimes crash you game if not used in certain ways.FixedNew shiny black UI, they've added a filter for housing - possibly to cater for the many mods which you can find in the workshop!! Good workshop integration as well.Multicore support and memory leaksGame goes haywire if you have a 300K+ city, this is due to several memory-leaks and 1 core utillization. The game runs as well on a pentium single core 4Ghz as it does on a 5970X.FIXEDCurrently I'm pushing 4 cores active on CXXL, memory usage is a steady 2.2GB and I must say the game is snappy as it can be so far!New content from developersVery little content is published by the developer and there is not much new stuff in terms of new housing, maps and blueprints. The variety of games features is heavily dependant on the work in our communityNot fixedHowever, they've implemented workshop -  which translates to a better way of adding mods to your game. Would have liked to see some more content anyway.Running issuesWhile they've improved plenty, there are also many issues here. Some are even newly introduced and others are adopted from back in the previous versions.Long roads are laggyIf you place long stretches of roads, it becomes laggy when you lay new roads intersecting these roads. It stutters a lot but is not unplayable. They should fix this very soon.BroadcastingBroadcasting can introduce some lagg as well, Especially when you try to zone large districts.Many cities slow tradingIf you a large amount of cities, it can have a slight effect on the trade menu.Savegames disapear/crash the gameI have already experienced savegame corruption and crashes from loading saves. To avoid this, do not use workshop yet. And do not download the community pack yet. There are issues which have deleted my savegames  (or they just disapeard from the load menu). And when I load pre-workshopped saves the game just crashes. This is a must solve as soon as possible..NEW:Instabillities while playingIf experienced more instabillities, the game is very laggy when deploying new Metro Systems or other routes for public transport. Once you lay more than 10 stations of metro, and have a few lines running allready, you will start get lags and other issues like problems to move about, long waits while calculations are done.Another point here is that it seems they have downtweaked the amount of people using the metro and bus systems, making it harder to maintain traffic flow and forcing you to be really smart when planning ahead for a new metro system. This can of course just be my imagination, but I feel that I need to be more careful now than in previous games.OmnicorpOmniCorp trading is just the same as before.NEW:New content worth mentioningIt's worth mentioning a few of the things new to this game in terms of content. Here are a few things i've come across so far:Farm ploppingIt looks to me as if they have tweaked the plopping of farming zones, it is easier to make irregular shaped farms around corners and along the boundries of the areas where farms can be plopped.TerrainTerrain responds better to changes done by development. For example, you will notice that laying out all types of zones in slopes and uneven terrain is easier and you experience less problems with road issues (Where roads cannot be constructed.) This is done by finding alternative paths for them in a more smooth way. I like it this way, makes more sense.Metro tubes disappears during gameplayIf you construct tubes with max amount of stations, they will just disappear after a while, leaving only the stations behind and potentionally crushing your infrastructure. This has to be fixed at some stage very soon!ConclusionAll in all, the game is a fresh breeze of cold air on a hot summer day.. Still there are a few issues here and there, surely these will be fixed in later patches for THIS game and not for future COMPLETE rewrites of the engine.For theTL;DRfolks out there, many of the problematic traffic, population and polution issues are solved. And I can confirm that it runs on all my cores and has so far not burned up all my memory (at a stable 2.2GB RAM) I'd buy it.I give the game a 8/10 in terms of its current state, and 6/10 for the hefty price -  considering the amount of money I have spent on previous broken titles. Owners of  two or more from the same title should have received 75% off of the price.I can warmly recommend this game for newbs to the CXL scene, for you guys who own other games like this, or is saving up for Cities> Skyline, have a look at the myriad of new gameplay>videos and decide for your self - i`d buy it."
