,Recommended,313010,33313681,Posted: 6 July,all,Bannor,"I have about 30 hours on this now, I think this is enough play-time for me to give my first impressions. I'm quite enjoying playing this, it's quite relaxing, interesting and challenging - all at the same time. It seems complex and in-depth enough, although this is my first city-builder game (I haven't played any other, so I've nothing to compare it to).Graphics seem good enough, although there's a graphical glitch where a swathe of green is spread across parts of the map (I think this is a problem with my now-aging system rather than the fault of the game).I like that I can play it at my own speed (and indeed, it seems that the slower one tries to progress, the more one is likely to succeed). I can see myself sinking MANY hours into this game - and not regretting any of them.If you're new to this genre or not sure about this game in particluar, I recommend buying it.[EDIT]I now have almost 150 hours play time in this game - and I'm absolutely loving it!  I don't understand all the negative reviews - and if you read most of them, they're not actually about this game being bad, or having any particular problem - it's about this game being released as a separate game, instead of a free update to owners of the previous incarnation of the game. ""This game sucks - just because I don't like the marketing strategy of the game publisher!"" - yeah, that's what they essentially boil down to.I really feel that you can't go wrong with giving this *excellent* game a try!"
