76561197999501275,Recommended,313010,14449521,"Posted: 13 February, 2015",all,Tynesider,"If your here reading these reviews, you'll have no doubt already read a billion reviews which state some or all of the following:- Nothing new about this- They just re-worked the GUI- Buttons are slightly different- I want a refundand it goes on.So why do i like this game ? firstly i got it for 50% off because i already own a previous copy of Cities XL and admittedly  it's hard to find much that is different, i have noticed the splash screen is different and some UI additions but that's not really a great selling point. The biggest selling point for me was, i got it for 50% off, the maps are massive and Steam workshop is intergrated now.Though It's clear that not much is different and it has enraged an entire population of steam consumers who wanted something new and if you want a completley new game, don't bother.Buy this game for it's size and Steam Workshop, the devs are clearly supporting the modding community with this one and if things continue to go forward, like it has, this will be one of those titles that really benefits from the fans and the developers support of the fans.I have not experienced any issues with this game and definitely none of this lag that some people are reporting.Cities XXL is a game about creating epic cityscapes that span what seems like entire continents. I love how everything comes together and exploring the city you have created is so rewarding, especially when you get down to the street level. Obviously having a powerful rig helps in this case and it is worth having one, just to experience it.For those of you who would like refunds, it's too late. This game needs to be played with an open mind, the maps are huge and varied, which all offer a very diverse set of challenges. The game engine has been improved and the detail that shines from your monitor is glorious to look at.This may look like Cities XL of old but if you just give it a chance and embrace the community around it, you will enjoy your time playing this. If you want a new game with the ability to micromanage every small detail of the cities execution find something else. Let the vast environments of XXL suck you in and just enjoy it, i do.Lastley i would like to add the following point. People are calling this a glorified patch for $20 but let's just agree to say it is and it would seem like a massive rip-off to all consumers to pay for a patch. Now, just think about every new game these days, they offer season passess for atleast $25 and map packs/skins new characters etc, some of which are extras outside the season pass inclusions. With this $20 patch, you get a new game engine, maps, challenges, buildings and workshop support, additionally whatever they decide to add later and it won't cost you anymore then $20. For a game to be released at such a low price and not even ask for a single cent more for content, you really can't beat that logic.Nb. i am expecting alot of hate for enjoying this game, i challenge those to just play it for a couple hours, you will like it."
