,Recommended,313010,14348260,"Posted: 5 February, 2015",all,dmozero2,"Ok... This game has gotten a lot of bad press from some very angry people, but I have to say... I LOVE THIS GAME!!!The positives:- The graphic are great!- Things are running smoothly on my machine- I like driving through my city and standing on top of buildings looking at what I've done- The farms are expansive- It's really fun seeing all the different buildings- It's challenging trying to balance the city needs, especially trying to solve traffic issues- I love that services are distance-based and not radial, and they have decent coverage- There are so many things to do and new things unlocking all the time- The tutorials help a LOT- I haven't encountered a single bug.The negatives:- The MUSIC... omg- It's lacking some flexibility with the roads (tight angles, on/off ramps... maybe I just haven't gotten that far)- I don't like having to bulldoze long stretches of roads to make minor tweaks and to upgrade roads.- It's more difficult than I thought to master the mechanics.- The ""look around"" feature with the mouse wheel is WAY too sensitive. It's an art form to pan where you want.- I wish I could choose whether or not to have suspension beams on my high-traffic viaducts.- It's kind of a pain having to drill down into each tool (and having it reset the default tool)The neutrals:- The controls are fine once you know how to use them, although some people are REALLY passionate about this.- The UI is intuitive and clean in my opinion. I used the tutorial so I know where everything is.Overall, I REALLY like this game so far, although I do get what people are saying about not being able to ""connect"" with the game. Something is lacking there, but I can't put my finger on it. Still I find it very enjoyable. I personally think the developers did a great job because the game is beautiful. I can imagine the challenges they went through. I think people are nitpicking over some very small things, but maybe I feel that way because I haven't owned a previous version of this game (and that was by choice, not from a lack of knowledge about the game)."
